# Environment variables that may not be assigned (standalone FOO=bar
# statements or per-command FOO=bar prefixes) in agent Bash commands,
# checked by the reject-obfuscated-commands hook. One glob pattern per
# line; blank lines and #-comments are ignored.
#
# Assigning any of these changes how OTHER commands are located, parsed, or
# attributed — word-splitting games (IFS), binary/loader hijack (PATH,
# LD_*), shell re-entry configuration (ENV, BASH_ENV), or git
# identity/config/transport tampering (GIT_*, the #1105 bypass class).

IFS
PATH
ENV
BASH_ENV
SHELL
SHELLOPTS
CDPATH
PS4
LD_PRELOAD
LD_LIBRARY_PATH
LD_AUDIT
PYTHONPATH
PYTHONSTARTUP
NODE_OPTIONS
GIT_*
